[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] If the first character in the *filename-search-pattern* is none of ‘***[?/**’ then it will be considered a substring match and will be implicitly surrounded by ‘*****’ (as in ******filename-search-pattern******).
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] If the subsequent string contains any of ‘***[?\**’, then it will handled like a glob pattern, otherwise any trailing ‘**/**’ or ‘**/.**’ will be removed and a literal path lookup will be performed.
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] The output format consists of one line per matching pattern, with a list of packages owning the pathname separated by a comma (U+002C ‘**,**’) and a space (U+0020 ‘’), followed by a colon (U+003A ‘**:**’) and a space, followed by the pathname.
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] entries are separated by an empty line, with the same order as specified on the argument list.
