[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] “**\**” before any other character suppresses any special meaning of the following character, which is useful for “**\**” and “**$**”.
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] Package information can be included by inserting variable references to package fields using the syntax “**${***field*[**;***width*]**}**”.
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] Fields are printed right-aligned unless the width is negative in which case left alignment will be used.
[src:dpkg/dpkg-query-1-en] It contains the binary package name with a possible architecture qualifier like “libc6:amd64” (since dpkg 1.16.2).
